# hermes-chat product scope

This repo is a **Hermes plugin chat interface**. Keep it simpler than competitor UIs.

## IN SCOPE

- Chat UI with streaming responses
- Tool-step display and decision gates (approval / clarify / sudo / secret) as native UI
- Light features: markdown rendering/editing, attachments, themes, session list, optional voice
- Plugin packaging, daemon lifecycle, JWT auth for the chat UI
- Same backend path as the built-in TUI: in-process `tui_gateway` JSON-RPC

## OUT OF SCOPE

Do **not** build or port these product surfaces (even if hermes-webui / hermes_client have them):

- Hermes settings / Control Center / provider setup wizards
- Interactive coding IDE or task boards
- Workspace file browser / Spaces / Memory.md admin panels
- Full cron / skills / plugins admin UIs
- Multi-profile agent management as a product feature
- xterm setup terminals for `hermes` config wizards

## UI stack

Prefer **assistant-ui** primitives (`@assistant-ui/react`, Thread / Composer / Message, tool UI, markdown) over custom chat chrome. Official assistant-ui skills live under `~/.agents/skills/` (`assistant-ui`, `primitives`, `runtime`, `tools`, `streaming`, `markdown`, …). Docs index: https://www.assistant-ui.com/llms.txt

## Reference materials

When improving chat UX or gateway integration, load project skills:

- `.cursor/skills/hermes-webui-reference` — steal chat patterns only
- `.cursor/skills/hermes-client-reference` — steal chat patterns only; never their auto-approve gates
- `.cursor/skills/hermes-home-reference` — local `hermes install/` + `tui_gateway` map (folder stays gitignored)
- `docs/hermes-gateway-protocol.md` — RPC/event catalog already derived from the install

When in doubt: if removing the feature would still leave a great chat app, it’s in scope; if it only exists to administer Hermes, leave it alone.
